"}, {"fieldtype": "Section Break", "label": ""}, {"fieldtype": "Column Break"}, {"fieldname": "_custom_html", "print_hide": 0, "label": "Custom HTML", "fieldtype": "HTML", "options": "<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <style>
    body {
      font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
      font-size: 13px;
      line-height: 1.6;
    }
    .section-title {
      font-weight: bold;
      margin-top: 20px;
    }
    .signature-table {
      width: 100%;
      border-collapse: collapse;
      font-size: 13px;
      margin-top: 40px;
      table-layout: fixed;
    }
    .signature-table td {
      border: 1px solid #555;
      padding: 15px;
      vertical-align: top;
      height: 200px;
      width: 50%;
    }
    .stamp-cell {
      height: 150px;
      text-align: center;
      vertical-align: middle;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>

    <table width="100%" cellspacing="20">
    <tr>
      <td valign="top" width="50%">
        <p><strong>Contract Ref#:</strong> {{ doc.custom_contract_reference }}</p>
        <p>This agreement is made on {{ doc.custom_contract_date }} (the "Effective Date") between:</p>

        <p><strong>{{ doc.party_name }}</strong>, hereinafter referred to as the <strong>FIRST PARTY</strong>, with:</p>
        <p>
          License No: {{ doc.custom_license_no }}<br>
          Address: {{ doc.custom_address }}<br>
          Tax Certificate No.: {{ doc.custom_tax_id }}
        </p>

        <p>AND</p>

        <p><strong>{{ doc.custom_company }}</strong>, hereinafter referred to as the <strong>SECOND PARTY</strong>, with:</p>
        <p>
          License No.: {{ doc.custom_license_no }}<br>
          P.O. Box: {{ doc.custom_po_box }}<br>
          Tel. No.: {{ doc.custom_tel_no }}<br>
          Fax No.: {{ doc.custom_fax_no }}<br>
          Tax Certificate No.: {{ doc.custom_with_tax_certificate_no }}
        </p>

        <p><strong>PROJECT SERVICES:</strong> {{ doc.custom_contract_type }}<br>
        <strong>PROJECT SITE LOCATION:</strong>
        {% set locs = doc.custom_project_site_locationss | map(attribute='location') | list %}
        {{ ", ".join(locs[:-1]) ~ (" & " ~ locs[-1] if locs|length > 1 else (locs[0] if locs else "")) }}
        </p>
        <p><strong>Section 1: Contract Term and Commencement</strong></p>
        <p>1.1 This Agreement shall be effective for a period of {{ doc.custom_contract_period }}, commencing on {{ doc.start_date }} and expiring on {{ doc.end_date }}.</p>
        <p>1.2 The Agreement shall automatically renew for successive terms unless either party provides {{ doc.custom_notice_period_before_expiration }} days’ written notice of non-renewal.</p>

        <p><strong>Section 2: Payments</strong></p>
        <p><strong>2.1 Payment Terms & Invoicing</strong><br>
        The FIRST PARTY shall pay the SECOND PARTY within {{ doc.custom_payment_term }} days from submission of the service receipt.<br>
        Credit notes (if applicable) will be issued by the SECOND PARTY.<br>
        Monthly invoices shall be submitted and are contestable within 7 days; otherwise deemed accepted.</p>
        <p><strong>Payment Details:</strong><br>
        Beneficiary Name: {{ doc.custom_beneficiary_name }}<br>
        Bank: {{ doc.custom_beneficiary_bank_name }}<br>
        Account No.: {{ doc.custom_beneficiary_account_number }}<br>
        IBAN: {{ doc.custom_beneficiary_iban }}</p>
        <p><strong>2.2 Disputed Invoices</strong><br>
        Partial payments to be made, with disputed amounts to be resolved by management or through Abu Dhabi courts.</p>
        <p><strong>2.2.a Late Payments</strong><br>
        SECOND PARTY may suspend services immediately if payments are delayed.</p>
        <p><strong>2.2.b Market Fluctuation</strong><br>
        With {{ doc.custom_notice_period_for_additional_charges }} days’ notice, SECOND PARTY may revise charges due to legal or market shifts.</p>
        <p><strong>2.2.c Tax</strong><br>
        All applicable taxes (e.g., VAT) shall be fully honored by the FIRST PARTY.</p>

        <p><strong>Section 3: Variations</strong></p>
        <p>Requests for service changes by FIRST PARTY shall be quoted and agreed upon in writing prior to implementation.</p>

        <p><strong>Section 4.1: FIRST PARTY Obligations</strong></p>
        <p>Access to premises<br>
        Prohibition on third-party use of SECOND PARTY assets<br>
        Exclusive assignment of services<br>
        Financial responsibility for damages<br>
        Compliance with TADWEER and regulatory guidelines<br>
        Accurate registration and reporting on waste manifests</p>
      </td>
      <td valign="top" width="50%">
        <p><strong>Section 4.2: SECOND PARTY Obligations</strong></p>
        <p>Vehicle assignment<br>
        Staff training<br>
        Monthly reports and documentation<br>
        Preventive maintenance<br>
        Compliance with DOH and TADWEER regulations</p>

        <p><strong>Section 5: Force Majeure</strong></p>
        <p>Parties are exempt from liability for delays due to events outside their control, with written notice within 7 days.</p>

        <p><strong>Section 6: Waiver</strong></p>
        <p>FIRST PARTY waives all claims against SECOND PARTY for damages unless explicitly provided for in this agreement.</p>

        <p><strong>Section 7: Confidentiality</strong></p>
        <p>All contractual matters shall remain confidential unless disclosure is required by law.</p>

        <p><strong>Section 8: Termination</strong></p>
        <p>Immediate termination due to default or insolvency<br>
        Termination due to inactivity beyond 2 months<br>
        Termination due to breach or failure to provide services<br>
        Mutual termination with 30 days’ notice</p>

        <p><strong>Section 9: Health and Safety</strong></p>
        <p>SECOND PARTY shall:<br>
        Follow Health & Safety laws and policies<br>
        Inform and cooperate with FIRST PARTY on all safety issues</p>

        <p><strong>Section 10: Assignment and Subcontracting</strong></p>
        <p>SECOND PARTY may assign or subcontract duties with or without FIRST PARTY’s consent.</p>

        <p><strong>Section 11: Intellectual Property Rights</strong></p>
        <p>All rights related to Orion IPR remain the sole property of Orion. FIRST PARTY may not use such rights without consent.</p>

        <p><strong>Section 12: Governing Law</strong></p>
        <p>This Agreement shall be governed by UAE law. Disputes shall be referred to Abu Dhabi courts.</p>

      </td>
    </tr>
  </table>
</body>
</html>
